The Johannesburg Roads Agency (JRA) will be undertaking repairs to bridge joints on the M1 double decker bridge over the weekend - on Saturday and Sunday, September 9 and 10. Traffic from Joburg south and west travelling northbound on the bridge will be affected and motorists have been asked to avoid the area.
JRA wishes to thank motorists in advance for their patience and understanding while this necessary repair work to bridge joints is being undertaken.
